        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1965-12-09T13:58:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1965-12-09T13:58:00-05:00" n="260"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d260">
                <head>260. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in India</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d260fn1">Source: National Archives and Records
                        Administration, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1964–66,
                            <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> (US) 15–8 INDIA. Confidential;
                        Flash. Drafted by Deputy Assistant <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>
                        Administrator Walter G. Farr, Jr., cleared by <persName corresp="#p_HWJ1"
                            >Handley</persName>, and approved by <persName corresp="#p_GWS1">William
                            S. Gaud</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1965-12-09T13:58:00-05:00">December 9, 1965, 1:58 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Aidto 747. Joint State-<gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> message.
                        Subject—<gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss> 480 and Fertilizer Loan. President
                    has just announced further extension <gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss> 480 Title
                    I program of 1,500,000 tons wheat for early shipment, that being equal to
                    present monthly allocation on three months basis. President also announced $50
                    million loan for urgent import fertilizer tied to <gloss target="#t_GOI1"
                        >GOI</gloss>
                    <pb facs="0537" n="499" xml:id="pg_499"/> expenditure like sum of own funds for
                    fertilizer import.<note n="2" xml:id="d260fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_MBD1">Bill Moyers</persName>, the President’s Press
                        Secretary, made these announcements on President <persName corresp="#p_JLB1"
                            >Johnson</persName>’s behalf in Austin, Texas on December 9. (<hi
                            rend="italic">American Foreign Policy: Current Documents, 1965</hi>, p.
                        754.) An amendment to the existing Title I <gloss target="#t_PL1"
                            >P.L.</gloss> 480 agreement with India, providing for an additional 1.5
                        million tons of foodgrains, was signed in New Delhi on December 10.
                        (Circular telegram 1133, December 11; National Archives and Records
                        Administration, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1964–66,
                            <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> (US) 15–8 INDIA)</note> President
                    believes all nations capable of helping should assist meet India’s present grave
                    food problem and indicated <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> would participate
                    fully. Full text Presidential announcement following.</p>
                <p>Inform Sen. Morse and other Senators and Congressmen in India of substance of
                    Presidential announcement.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>. Pleased <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss>
                    announcement own plans import $79 million fertilizer. Every effort should be
                    made assure <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> loan entirely supplemental to
                    maximum effort by <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> to import fertilizer with
                    other than <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> funds. Loan will also be tied in
                    to overall agricultural program. By exchange of letters or otherwise, <gloss
                        target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> will be expected agree to certain specific
                    self-help efforts, particularly in private sector production and distribution
                    fertilizer and other inputs. Detailed negotiating instructions follow. <gloss
                        target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Rusk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
